{{NCAATeamFootballSeason |Year=1995 |Team=Texas A&M Aggies |Image= |ImageSize= |Conference=Southwest Conference |Division= |ShortConference=SWC |CoachRank=15 |APRank=15 |Record=9-3 |ConfRecord=5-2 |HeadCoach=[[R.C. Slocum]] |StadiumArena=[[Kyle Field]] |Champion=Alamo Bowl Champions |BowlTourney= [[1995 Alamo Bowl|Alamo Bowl]] vs. [[1995 Michigan Wolverines football team|Michigan]] |BowlTourneyResult= Won 22-20 }} {{1995 Southwest Conference football standings}} The '''1995 [[Texas A&M Aggies]] football team''' completed the season with a 9-3 record. The Aggies had a regular season [[Southwest Conference]] record of 5-2.
1995 was the final year of the Southwest Conference. At the end of the season A&M, along with [[Texas Tech University|Texas Tech]], [[Baylor University|Baylor]], and [[University of Texas at Austin|Texas]], would combine with the members of the [[Big 8 Conference]] to form the [[Big 12 Conference]], which began play in 1996.
